                           SECTION 1: DEFINITIONS
================================================================================

For purposes of this Agreement, the following terms shall have the meanings
set forth below:

1.1  "Software" means the BEVoid project, including but not limited to all
     source code files, object code, compiled binaries, libraries, modules,
     plugins, extensions, APIs, SDKs, documentation, user interfaces,
     graphics, data files, configuration files, scripts, build systems,
     and any other materials provided by Licensor.

1.2  "Derivative Work" means any modification, adaptation, translation,
     revision, enhancement, improvement, derivative, or other work based
     upon or incorporating the Software, in whole or in part.

1.3  "Distribution" means any transfer, conveyance, sale, lease, license,
     sublicense, gift, assignment, or other disposition of the Software
     or any Derivative Work, whether for value or without consideration.

1.4  "Commercial Use" means any use of the Software that is intended for
     or results in commercial advantage, monetary compensation, or
     financial gain, whether direct or indirect.

1.5  "Malicious Use" means any use of the Software that is intended to
     cause harm, damage, or unauthorized access to computer systems,
     networks, data, or services.

1.6  "Authorized Purpose" means personal, non-commercial use of the
     Software for educational purposes, research, or private
     experimentation, excluding any Malicious Use or Commercial Use.

1.7  "Intellectual Property Rights" means all patents, copyrights,
     trademarks, trade secrets, moral rights, database rights, design
     rights, and any other intellectual property rights worldwide.

1.8  "Contributor" means any individual or entity that has contributed
     code, documentation, or other materials to the BEVoid Project.

