================================================================================

You are expressly authorized to use the Software only in the following ways:

3.1  **Personal Educational Use**: You may use the Software to learn about
     software architecture, development practices, and related technical
     concepts.

3.2  **Private Research**: You may conduct private, non-commercial research
     using the Software, provided that such research does not violate any
     applicable laws, regulations, or third-party rights.

3.3  **Academic Study**: Students and educators at accredited educational
     institutions may use the Software for coursework, thesis projects,
     or classroom instruction, provided that such use is non-commercial
     and properly attributed.

3.4  **Personal Experimentation**: You may modify the Software for your
     own personal experimentation and learning, provided that such
     modifications are not Distributed.

3.5  **Security Research**: You may conduct security research on the
     Software following responsible disclosure practices as outlined
     in Section 56, provided that such research is conducted ethically
     and legally.

3.6  **Bug Reporting**: You may report bugs, vulnerabilities, or issues
     to Licensor through official channels.

3.7  **Backup and Archival**: You may make backup copies as expressly
     permitted in Section 2.2, provided that such copies are kept
     secure and not used for any unauthorized purpose.

