                    SECTION 70: STATUTORY DAMAGES
================================================================================

70.1 **Availability**: Statutory damages shall be
     available where provided by law.

70.2 **Copyright**: Statutory damages for copyright
     infringement shall be available under applicable
     law.

70.3 **Willfulness**: Willful infringement may
     result in enhanced statutory damages.

70.4 **Innocence**: Innocent infringement may result
     in reduced statutory damages.

70.5 **Election**: Plaintiff may elect statutory
     damages instead of actual damages.

================================================================================
                     SECTION 71: ACTUAL DAMAGES
================================================================================

71.1 **Compensatory**: Actual damages shall
     compensate for proven losses.

71.2 **Direct**: Direct damages flow directly from
     the breach.

71.3 **Proof**: Actual damages must be proven with
     evidence.

71.4 **Foreseeability**: Damages must have been
     foreseeable at the time of contracting.

71.5 **Causation**: There must be causal connection
     between breach and damages.

================================================================================
                   SECTION 72: CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES
================================================================================

72.1 **Exclusion**: CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES ARE
     EXCLUDED AS PROVIDED IN SECTION 14.

72.2 **Definition**: Consequential damages include
     indirect, incidental, and special damages.

72.3 **Examples**: Examples include lost profits,
     lost data, and business interruption.

72.4 **Exception**: Consequential damages may be
     recoverable for willful misconduct.

72.5 **Waiver**: You waive any right to consequential
     damages to the extent permitted by law.

================================================================================
                    SECTION 73: PUNITIVE DAMAGES
================================================================================

73.1 **Availability**: Punitive damages may be
     available for willful, malicious, or fraudulent
     conduct.

73.2 **Standard**: Punitive damages require clear
     and convincing evidence of wrongful conduct.

73.3 **Ratio**: Punitive damages shall bear
     reasonable ratio to actual damages.

73.4 **Caps**: Punitive damages shall be subject to
     statutory caps where applicable.

73.5 **Insurance**: Punitive damages may not be
     insurable.

================================================================================
                    SECTION 74: LIQUIDATED DAMAGES
================================================================================

74.1 **Agreement**: Parties agree that certain
     damages may be difficult to calculate.

74.2 **Reasonable Estimate**: Liquidated damages
     shall be a reasonable estimate of actual
     damages.

74.3 **Not Penalty**: Liquidated damages shall not
     be a penalty.

74.4 **Exclusive**: Liquidated damages may be the
     exclusive remedy for certain breaches.

74.5 **Cumulative**: Liquidated damages may be
     cumulative with other remedies.

================================================================================
                       SECTION 75: RESTITUTION
================================================================================

75.1 **Availability**: Restitution may be available
     to prevent unjust enrichment.

75.2 **Measure**: Restitution shall be measured by
     benefit conferred.

75.3 **Return**: Restitution may require return of
     property or benefits.

75.4 **Offset**: Restitution may be offset by
     damages.

75.5 **Equitable**: Restitution is an equitable
     remedy.

================================================================================
                      SECTION 76: DISGORGEMENT
================================================================================

76.1 **Availability**: Disgorgement may be available
     for willful breaches.

76.2 **Measure**: Disgorgement shall be measured by
     profits gained.

76.3 **Calculation**: Profits shall be calculated
     net of expenses.

76.4 **Burden**: The burden of proving expenses
     shall be on the breaching party.

76.5 **Cumulative**: Disgorgement may be cumulative
     with other remedies.

================================================================================
                    SECTION 77: ACCOUNT OF PROFITS
================================================================================

77.1 **Availability**: Account of profits may be
     available for intellectual property
     infringement.

77.2 **Scope**: Account shall include all profits
     attributable to infringement.

77.3 **Records**: Breaching party shall provide
     records for accounting.

77.4 **Expert**: An expert may be appointed to
     conduct accounting.

77.5 **Costs**: Costs of accounting shall be
     borne by breaching party.

================================================================================
                   SECTION 78: DESTRUCTION OF COPIES
